[[Brigadier]] '''Donald David Graeme Hardie''' [[Royal Victorian Order|CVO]] [[Territorial Decoration|TD]] [[Venerable Order of Saint John|KStJ]] (born 23 January 1936) is a Scottish businessman and retired [[Territorial Army (United Kingdom)|Territorial Army]] officer. He was [[Lord Lieutenant of Dunbartonshire]] from 1990 to 2007. He is also an honorary vice-president of Lennox and Argyll Battalion of the [[Boys' Brigade]], and is the Keeper of [[Dumbarton Castle]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.helensburghadvertiser.co.uk/articles/1/29829 |title=St John members raise charity cash |work=Helensburgh Advertiser |date=23 October 2008 |accessdate=2 December 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005203359/http://www.helensburghadvertiser.co.uk/articles/1/29829 |archivedate=5 October 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

Hardie was appointed [[Commander of the Royal Victorian Order]] (CVO) in 2008.<ref>Biography, ''[[Who's Who]]''</ref>

