[[File:Karl Glad.jpg|thumb|right|200 px |Karl Glad]]
'''Karl Glad''' (born 26 September 1937) is a Norwegian jurist and industrialist. He was born in [[Oslo]]. He served as manager of [[Aker ASA|Akergruppen]] from 1980 to 1987,  and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of Aker AS from 1989 to 1991. He was manager of the [[Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise]] from 1991 to 1999.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Karl Glad |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Karl_Glad|language=Norwegian |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Karl Glad |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Karl |last=Nysterud |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Karl_Glad/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=9 March 2012 }}</ref>

