'''Lin Wei-shan''' ({{zh|t=林蔚山}}) is a [[Taiwanese people|Taiwanese]] business man. He is the present chairman and president of [[Tatung Company]], which his grandfather {{ill|Lin Shan-chih|zh|林煶灶}} founded in 1918. He took over the presidency from his father {{ill|Lin Ting-sheng|zh|林挺生}} on 17 March 2006.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=zh:大同接班完成 林蔚山接任董座 |url=http://www.epochtimes.com/b5/6/3/17/n1257877.htm |publisher=[[Epoch Times]] |date=March 17, 2007 |language=Chinese }}</ref> However, his wife {{ill|Lin Kuo Wen-yen|zh|林郭文艷}} is widely considered as the de facto executor in Tatung.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=zh:長媳林郭文豔 大同新生推手 |url=http://www.libertytimes.com.tw/2005/new/mar/31/today-stock7.htm |publisher=[[Liberty Times]] |date=March 31, 2005 |language=Chinese }}</ref>
