{{Infobox university |name = Sukkur IBA University |native_name = |image_name = SIBA Logo.jpeg |image_size = 300 px |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = ''Merit, Quality, Excellence'' |established = 1994 |closed = |endowment = |vice_chancellor = Prof. Nisar Ahmed Siddique |staff = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |other = |city = [[Sukkur]] |state = |province = [[Sindh]] |country = {{PAK}} |coor = |campus = |former_names = |free_label = |free = |affiliations = |website = {{Website|iba-suk.edu.pk}} |logo = |footnotes = }}
The '''Sukkur IBA University''' (''previously'' '''Sukkur Institute of Business Administration''' or '''Sukkur IBA''') ({{lang-sd|'''سکر آئي بي اي يونيورسٽي'''}}) is a higher education institute in [[Sukkur]], [[Pakistan]]. The university is a public sector degree-awarding institute chartered by the [[Government of Sindh]] and recognized by the Higher Education Commission.
==History==
In 1994, the school was established as '''Sukkur Institute of Business Administration'''. It was located initially in hired rooms of Public School Sukkur building in Sukkur. At first, Sukkur IBA was affiliated to [[Institute of Business Administration, Karachi]]; with founding Director Professor Dr. Syed Anwar Ali Shah (Present Pro-Vice Chancellor University of Sindh) the institute received its full charter from the Government of Sindh in 2006, creating an opportunity for the Sindhi youth. The institute is ranked 3rd among the five independent business schools of Pakistan included in the Higher Education Commission Pakistan Business School Ranking-2013).<ref>[http://www.paked.net/higher_education/hec_university_rankings.htm : Higher Education Commission (HEC) ranking]</ref>
On 16 May 2017, [[Provincial Assembly of Sindh|Sindh Assembly]] approved promotion of institute from Sukkur IBA to Sukkur IBA University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nation.com.pk/karachi/16-May-2017/sa-approves-iba-university-in-sukkur|title=SA approves IBA university in Sukkur|last=Nation|first=The|date=16 May 2017|website=Nation PK|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
==Departments== [[File:Sukkur IBA University - academic block I (2).jpg|thumb|200px|Academic Block-I at SIBAU]] The university has five main departments: # Faculty of Business Administration # Faculty of Computer Science # Faculty of Education Management # Faculty of Electrical Engineering # Faculty of Mathematics
